<title type="html"><![CDATA[Flipping background tiles?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5850&amp;p=54173#p54173"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Note that if you have CHR-RAM it's always possible to flip tiles in software. I know it still wastes VRAM, but at least it doesn't waste ROM.<br /></div><br />I've seen SMS games doing that with sprites. When copying the tiles from ROM to VRAM, a 256-byte long table was used to flip every byte during the copy for horizontal flipping. Also, I believe they read the tiles upside down (bottom row first) for vertical flipping.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Fri Dec 18, 2009 7:32 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
