<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5850&amp;p=54165#p54165"><![CDATA[
Interesting, I guess the GBC also have the ability to flip BG tiles and have background priority which is an extra to what the NES can do.<br /><br />Note that if you have CHR-RAM it's always possible to flip tiles in software. I know it still wastes VRAM, but at least it doesn't waste ROM.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Fri Dec 18, 2009 1:58 pm</p><hr />
